text.tspan: Internal Components
In this section, the system is described in its implementation.
We have divided the explanation into
two parts, the first referring to the part implemented
in Java and the second referring to the rules
implemented in prolog.
Java Classes
Here we will describe how the implemented Java application
works, as well as the implementation of
the classes and methods we have developed.
MAIN
This class acts as an entry point for the system.
This class instantiates a SWING interface with two
buttons, both instantiating a new (JFrame) class,
which results in a new window opening.
The buttons are respectively:
“Graph From Text” which opens a new window (instantiating
the class GraphTextFrame)
which allows the user to execute the pipeline, from
the specified input text.
